arn.description: The ARN of the traffic mirror target.

description.description: A description of the traffic mirror session.

gatewayLoadBalancerEndpointId.description: The VPC Endpoint Id of the Gateway Load Balancer that is associated with the target.

networkInterfaceId.description: The network interface ID that is associated with the target.

networkLoadBalancerArn.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Network Load Balancer that is associated with the target.

ownerId.description: The ID of the AWS account that owns the traffic mirror target.

tags.description:
Key-value map of resource tags. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

**NOTE:** Either `network_interface_id` or `network_load_balancer_arn` should be specified and both should not be specified together

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
